('required-secure-branch-network-project', 'secure-connectivity-and-defense', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Secure Branch Network Project', 'Milestone project: Build a branch network with segmentation, firewall rules, VPN access, secure management, and logging.', 9, 'side', 4, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Build a branch network with segmentation, firewall rules, VPN access, secure management, and logging.","buildSteps":["Define the Secure Branch Network Project scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: network path, firewall rules.","Draw the topology, addressing plan, trust boundaries, and expected packet path.","Configure or simulate the network behavior required by the project brief.","Verify connectivity, routing, DNS, filtering, or failure behavior with commands and captured outputs.","Document the final topology, commands used, observed results, and unresolved risks.","Keep the scope focused enough to complete, review, and explain the a Secure Branch Network Project network design, configuration lab, or troubleshooting write-up.","Document how to run or review the Secure Branch Network Project deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/network-engineer","nodeKey":"required-secure-branch-network-project"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Network Security through a focused Secure Branch Network Project artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a Secure Branch Network Project network design, configuration lab, or troubleshooting write-up is available for review.","The Secure Branch Network Project scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
