('optional-specialization-lab', 'choose-network-specializations', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Specialization Lab', 'Optional practice project: Build a focused lab around one chosen specialization such as EVPN/VXLAN, Kubernetes networking, SD-WAN, or IPv6.', 11, 'side', 5, 'advanced', '{"whatToBuild":"Build a focused lab around one chosen specialization such as EVPN/VXLAN, Kubernetes networking, SD-WAN, or IPv6.","buildSteps":["Define the Specialization Lab scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: cluster workload.","Draw the topology, addressing plan, trust boundaries, and expected packet path.","Configure or simulate the network behavior required by the project brief.","Verify connectivity, routing, DNS, filtering, or failure behavior with commands and captured outputs.","Document the final topology, commands used, observed results, and unresolved risks.","Document how to run or review the Specialization Lab deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/network-engineer","nodeKey":"optional-specialization-lab"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply CI/CD through a focused Specialization Lab artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a Specialization Lab network design, configuration lab, or troubleshooting write-up is available for review.","The Specialization Lab scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
